## 4. The "Hand Feel" Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Medium-Hard (47.5 ESN). Feels slightly softer than MX-P despite identical sponge hardness due to the more elastic topsheet.
    - Feedback: Very clear and crisp. You know exactly where the ball hit the racket.
    - Hold vs. Release: Pronounced "Hold" feeling. The ball sinks into the topsheet deeply before the sponge kicks it out.
    - Dwell Time: High. It feels like you carry the ball on the racket for a split second longer than most offensive rubbers.

- Sound/Click
    - Produces a satisfying, sharp "click" when engaged properly, reminiscent of the speed glue era, though slightly less loud than FX-P.

