## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon: Exceptional match. Blades like Viscaria or Timo Boll ALC tame the high arc of EL-S and provide the stiffness needed for explosive power.
    - Inner Carbon: Great for heavily spin-oriented players who want maximum dwell time and high safety margins.
    - All-Wood: Works well with stiffer 7-ply woods (e.g., Clipper). Might feel too mushy on flexible 5-ply woods.
    - Mismatch Cases: Avoid very soft, slow 5-ply blades, as the setup will become overly bouncy without enough power to finish the point.

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand: Excellent choice for players who prioritize spin and safety over pure flat speed.
    - Backhand: Fantastic for advanced players who possess strong backhand mechanics and rely heavily on the Chiquita and backhand loop.

